ZH: 这个士兵正在行礼向上级致敬。
EN: The soldier is saluting his superior.

ZH: 在学校的操场上，学生们行礼迎接校长的到来。
EN: On the school playground, students are saluting to welcome the principal.

ZH: 在军事训练中，士兵必须按规定的姿势行礼。
EN: During military training, soldiers must salute in the prescribed posture.

ZH: 每天早晨，学生们进校门前要行礼致敬国旗。
EN: Every morning, students have to salute the flag before entering the school gates.

ZH: 行礼时要保持肩平手握拳头的姿势。
EN: When saluting, you should maintain the posture with shoulders level and fists clenched.

ZH: 在国际场合，外交官需要行礼向对方表示敬意。
EN: Diplomats need to salute to show respect on international occasions.

ZH: 在婚礼上，新人们向父母行礼以表示感激和尊敬。
EN: At weddings, the couple bows to their parents to show gratitude and respect.

ZH: 在运动会上，获奖的运动员会行礼致敬奏国歌。
EN: At sports competitions, winning athletes will salute and play the national anthem.

ZH: 士兵们在阅兵式上整齐划一地行礼致敬领导。
EN: The soldiers salute the leaders in a uniform and orderly manner during the parade.

ZH: 前来悼念的人们纷纷行礼致敬，表示对逝者的敬意。
EN: People who come to mourn pay their respects and salute to show their reverence for the deceased.

ZH: 在宴会上，主人会行礼向来宾表示欢迎与敬意。
EN: At banquets, the host will bow and salute to welcome and show respect to the guests.

ZH: 他来到长者身旁，恭敬地行礼向他问好。
EN: He walked up to the elder and respectfully saluted him to say hello.

ZH: 在仪式上，学生代表会行礼表达对老师的敬意。
EN: During the ceremony, student representatives will bow to show respect to the teachers.

ZH: 在传统文化中，年长者行礼代表尊重和恭敬。
EN: In traditional culture, bowing to elders represents respect and reverence.

ZH: 教官严肃地看着学员们行礼，要求他们保持仪态。
EN: The instructor watches the students salute seriously and demands that they maintain proper behavior.

ZH: 当国旗升起时，大家会齐刷刷地行礼致敬。
EN: When the national flag is raised, everyone will salute in unison.

ZH: 小朋友们在学校会集时，会按照老师的要求行礼。
EN: When the children gather at school, they will salute according to the teacher's instructions.

ZH: 在节日里，人们会相互行礼祝贺，并彼此表示祝福。
EN: During festivals, people will salute each other to congratulate and express their blessings.

ZH: 作为对手方的尊重，运动员会行礼致敬对手。
EN: As a sign of respect for the opponents, athletes will salute and pay their respects to their opponents.

ZH: 他站直身体，然后行礼向领导报告工作情况。
EN: He stood upright and then saluted the leader to report on the work situation.
